    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the implementation plan I've built:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `Bun.INI` namespace\n\n### What I found\n\n- All format namespaces (`TOML`, `JSONC`, `JSON5`, `YAML`) follow an identical 6-part wiring pattern\n- An internal INI parser exists at `src/ini.zig`, but must NOT be reused (per requirements) — the new `INIObject.zig` must be self-contained\n- There is also a 6th registration point I discovered: **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** re-exports all the Object modules, so that needs updating too\n\n### 6 files to change\n\n| # | File | Change |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | **CREATE** `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | Self-contained `parse` (line-by-line: comments, `[section]`, `key=value`) + `stringify` (scalars first, then `[section]` blocks) |\n| 2 | `src/bun.js/api.zig` | Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| 3 | `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | 4 micro-edits: lazy prop constant, `@export(...)`, getter function, import |\n| 4 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI)` between `Glob` and `JSON5` |\n| 5 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add `INI   BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI   DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to the hash table |\n| 6 | `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` with JSDoc + examples after `namespace TOML` |",
